            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Fixed by postponing the msg_showcmd event until after the `\"` is cleared:\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/edit.c b/src/nvim/edit.c\nindex d6373f9c49..8848573d8b 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/edit.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/edit.c\n@@ -3270,13 +3270,13 @@ static void ins_reg(void)\n     ins_need_undo = true;\n   }\n   u_sync_once = 0;\n-  clear_showcmd();\n \n   // If the inserted register is empty, we need to remove the '\"'\n   if (need_redraw || stuff_empty()) {\n     edit_unputchar();\n   }\n \n+  clear_showcmd();\n   // Disallow starting Visual mode here, would get a weird mode.\n   if (!vis_active && VIsual_active) {\n     end_visual_mode();\n```\n\nextui should also be fine not immediately updating the screen for an empty msg_showcmd event, that should always be followed by a regular redraw (I think).",
